2  Fast Energy Region                                             4025 1451
=====================                                             4025 1451
                                                                  4025 1451
   Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical analysis     4025 1451
utilizing available experimental data and nuclear reaction model  4025 1451
calculations.                                                     4025 1451
  Available experimental data were interpreted using nuclear      4025 1451
reaction model code EMPIRE-3 by M. Herman et al [1]. This code    4025 1451
integrates into a single system a number of important modules     4025 1451
and features:                                                     4025 1451
   - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including               4025 1451
   coupled-channels (ECIS06 by J. Raynal)                         4025 1451
   - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including HRTW width       4025 1451
   fluctuation correction                                         4025 1451
   - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION & TRISTAN by   4025 1451
   H. Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                                 4025 1451
   - Exciton model with angular momentum coupling (code DEGAS by  4025 1451
   E. Betak and P. Oblozinsky) that represents a good             4025 1451
   approximation to the DSD model                                 4025 1451
   - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster emission and       4025 1451
   Kalbach systematic angular distr. (code PCROSS by R.Capote et  4025 1451
   al)                                                            4025 1451
   - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of each particle,  4025 1451
   including realistic treatment of discrete transitions          4025 1451
   - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [2]                 4025 1451
   - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses, level        4025 1451
   density, discrete levels, fission barriers and gamma strength  4025 1451
   functions based on the RIPL library [2]                        4025 1451
   - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the            4025 1451
   EXFOR/CSISRS library                                           4025 1451
   - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A. Trkov) coupled to       4025 1451
   graphical presentation capabilities (code ZVView by V.         4025 1451
   Zerkin) through the chain of PrePro codes by R. Cullen         4025 1451
   - Checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                      4025 1451
   - Support for NJOY                                             4025 1451
