3  Resonance Region                                               4025 1451
===================                                               4025 1451
                                                                  4025 1451
   The original resonance region evaluation was performed in      4025 1451
October 2006 by S.F. Mughabghab (BNL) for ENDF/B-VII.0. The       4025 1451
resolved resonance parameters are adopted from the ATLAS [4].     4025 1451
This evaluation was revised in January 2011 by S.F. Mughabghab    4025 1451
(BNL) when a bound level at -234 eV removed from previous         4025 1451
evaluation.                                                       4025 1451
  The ENDF/B.VII.0 thermal capture cross section, 77 mb, was      4025 1451
taken from the Atlas recommendations [4]. This value was          4025 1451
obtained by the subtraction method, so a thermal capture cross    4025 1451
section of 0.830 +/- 0.083 b for 91Zr was adopted, based on the   4025 1451
measurements of Lone [5]. A more recent measurement by Nakaruma   4025 1451
et al. [6] reported a low limit of 1.30 +/- 0.04 b for the        4025 1451
thermal capture cross section of 91Zr indicating that the         4025 1451
derived thermal capture cross section for 90Zr is                 4025 1451
over-estimated. Therefore, we removed the bound level at -234 eV  4025 1451
but otherwise adopted the ENDF/B-VII.0 resonances. The computed   4025 1451
thermal capture cross section from the positive-energy            4025 1451
resonances is 10 mb, which is in good agreement within the        4025 1451
uncertainty limits with a measured value of 14+8-4 mb [5]. We     4025 1451
truncated the resolved resonance region at 53.5 keV.              4025 1451
